to the editor re city museum is accused of altering its aids exhibit news article april 27 as the curators of aids a living archive we certainly agree with the implicit message of your article opposition to the fostering of sanitized art by mayor rudolph w giuliani 's decency commission but we are very disappointed by the suggestion that your readers would be less compelled by what did make it into the show based on our 18 years documenting and producing educational materials about aids than by what the museum of the city of new york censored censorship issues are indeed petrifying meanwhile the aids pandemic rages on killing millions worldwide our agenda as curators is to provide a public forum to commemorate the dead educate the living and fight for a world without aids jean carlomusto jane rosett new york may 1 2001

